WEBVTT

00:28.028 --> 00:30.030
♪ ♪

00:55.139 --> 00:57.141
♪ ♪

01:11.155 --> 01:13.157
♪ ♪

01:31.759 --> 01:33.761
♪ ♪

01:57.076 --> 01:59.411
♪ ♪

02:01.872 --> 02:04.083
(dings)

02:04.166 --> 02:06.168
(birds chirping)

02:08.462 --> 02:10.464
Good morning, Mother and Father.

02:10.548 --> 02:12.675
Good morning, Tinashe.

02:12.758 --> 02:14.426
Good morning, Mother and Father.

02:14.510 --> 02:16.262
Good morning, Omma.

02:16.345 --> 02:19.181
Good morning, Mother and Father,
and happy anniversary.

02:19.265 --> 02:21.475
Yes, Meeka.

02:21.559 --> 02:24.144
It is our anniversary.

02:24.228 --> 02:25.771
(crowd cheering)

02:25.855 --> 02:28.190
AKEEM:
Today, we celebrate

02:28.274 --> 02:31.777
30 years of Zamundan prosperity,

02:31.861 --> 02:35.531
30 years of service
to our great nation

02:35.614 --> 02:39.535
and 30 years
of delicious fast food.

02:39.618 --> 02:43.122
-We want to welcome you all to
McDowell's Zamunda. -(cheering)

02:46.208 --> 02:49.044
The McDowell's menu is in no way

02:49.128 --> 02:51.505
influenced by
the McDonald's menu.

02:51.589 --> 02:53.424
They've got Egg McMuffins.

02:53.507 --> 02:55.301
We've got Egg McStuffins.

02:55.384 --> 02:56.969
MAURICE:
We are also celebrating

02:57.052 --> 03:02.391
the arrival of our new
Beyond Big Mick Burger!

03:02.474 --> 03:06.312
And it's all part of my lovely
granddaughter's campaign

03:06.395 --> 03:08.522
to reduce our, uh... our what?

03:08.606 --> 03:10.149
Carbon footprint.

03:10.232 --> 03:13.360
And without using
any animal by-products.

03:13.444 --> 03:16.238
It's just
good old-fashioned grass.

03:18.449 --> 03:20.451
-So there's no meat?
-There's no meat.

03:22.077 --> 03:24.747
MAURICE:
Beautiful, leafy taste.

03:24.830 --> 03:26.916
So delicious.

03:26.999 --> 03:29.043
Maybe it would taste
much better with a...

03:29.126 --> 03:31.795
(coughs) Pepsi.

03:31.879 --> 03:35.799
Pepsi, the official soft drink
of McDowell's Zamunda.

03:35.883 --> 03:38.093
-(chuckling)
-(camera clicking)

03:39.345 --> 03:41.639
-(grunting)
-(rhythmic drumming)

03:50.105 --> 03:51.440
(grunting)

04:01.909 --> 04:03.577
(panting)

04:03.661 --> 04:05.079
You look tired, Father.

04:05.162 --> 04:07.623
Maybe he needs a nap.

04:11.001 --> 04:13.045
I am the heir
to the throne of Zamunda.

04:13.128 --> 04:15.339
I shall not be shamed
by my two daughters.

04:15.422 --> 04:16.590
TINASHE:
Three daughters!

04:16.674 --> 04:18.050
(yells)

04:19.218 --> 04:20.260
(grunting fiercely)

04:34.525 --> 04:35.609
(chuckles)

04:35.693 --> 04:37.444
-Yeah!
-(excited chatter)

04:37.528 --> 04:40.531
Behold! Prince Akeem
in his natural element,

04:40.614 --> 04:43.826
cowering at the mercy
of the women in his life.

04:43.909 --> 04:45.869
Semmi, perhaps you would like
to spar with my daughters

04:45.953 --> 04:47.538
and teach them
some combinations.

04:48.580 --> 04:49.999
(chuckles) No doubt, you are

04:50.082 --> 04:51.500
their best teacher,
Your Majesty.

04:51.583 --> 04:52.876
It is my daughters that teach me

04:52.960 --> 04:54.211
in the languages
of the modern world.

04:54.294 --> 04:55.921
For instance,

04:56.005 --> 04:57.631
are my princely robes
not on fleek?

04:57.715 --> 05:00.259
Oh, my God, Father.
To be on fleek is no more.

05:00.342 --> 05:01.885
Really?

05:03.512 --> 05:05.014
I rather enjoyed being on fleek.

05:05.097 --> 05:06.557
SEMMI:
Your father has sent for you.

05:06.640 --> 05:08.892
He has an urgent matter
to discuss with you.

05:08.976 --> 05:12.021
Tell me, Semmi,
this urgent matter--

05:12.104 --> 05:14.648
does it concern
my marriage to a suitor

05:14.732 --> 05:17.151
who shall one day sit
on the throne of Zamunda?

05:17.234 --> 05:19.028
I will talk to Father alone.

05:24.324 --> 05:26.452
And how is my father today?

05:26.535 --> 05:29.079
He has already ordered
my execution three times.

05:29.163 --> 05:31.415
Oh, then he must be
feeling better. (chuckles)

05:31.498 --> 05:32.666
Prince Akeem!

05:32.750 --> 05:34.418
Nexdorian soldiers.

05:34.501 --> 05:36.462
I could not stop.
They are coming.

05:38.839 --> 05:40.841
♪ ♪

05:54.605 --> 05:55.898
(soldiers shout in unison)

05:55.981 --> 06:01.528
Presenting the supreme leader
of Nexdoria,

06:01.612 --> 06:04.865
the conqueror of countries
and hearts...

06:04.948 --> 06:05.949
(soldiers grunt in unison)

06:06.033 --> 06:07.910
...the wrestler of lions,

06:07.993 --> 06:10.079
the tamer of elephants,

06:10.162 --> 06:12.664
the inspiration for Mufasa...

06:12.748 --> 06:16.043
(soldiers roar)

06:16.126 --> 06:21.423
...the most well-endowed man
in Africa,

06:21.507 --> 06:24.051
General...

06:24.134 --> 06:26.386
Izzi.

06:38.649 --> 06:41.485
Prince Akeem.

06:41.568 --> 06:43.487
Whoa, look at you.

06:43.570 --> 06:45.989
(Izzi chuckles)

06:46.073 --> 06:51.036
My condolences this day
for your father, the king.

06:51.120 --> 06:53.914
Many thanks for your
well wishes, General Izzi,

06:53.997 --> 06:56.291
but as you know,
my father still breathes.

06:56.375 --> 06:59.670
Barely, but for how long?

06:59.753 --> 07:01.380
Why have you come here, General?

07:01.463 --> 07:03.841
30 years ago,
you left my sister at the altar.

07:03.924 --> 07:05.300
Oh, here we go.

07:05.384 --> 07:06.385
Now look at she.

07:06.468 --> 07:09.513
(high-pitched barking)

07:12.182 --> 07:14.685
Imani, always a pleasure.

07:14.768 --> 07:16.145
(snarls)

07:16.228 --> 07:20.482
If you had married her,
our countries would be united,

07:20.566 --> 07:23.735
putting an end to decades
of suffering for all our people.

07:23.819 --> 07:25.362
AKEEM:
General, throughout the years,

07:25.445 --> 07:27.990
we have tried to help
Nexdoria many times.

07:28.073 --> 07:30.951
I would like nothing more
than to help your country

07:31.034 --> 07:32.828
relieve its burden of poverty.

07:32.911 --> 07:36.081
Zamunda can only afford so much.

07:36.165 --> 07:38.625
I did not come here for money.

07:38.709 --> 07:41.128
I came here for blood.

07:43.505 --> 07:45.299
But not the murder kind.

07:45.382 --> 07:47.801
No, no, no, family blood.

07:47.885 --> 07:50.220
Marriage blood, yes?

07:51.930 --> 07:57.060
Has your daughter considered
the proposal from my son?

07:57.144 --> 07:59.396
Hey, Prince-o. (chuckles)

07:59.479 --> 08:01.148
My fellow player.

08:01.231 --> 08:02.858
Hey!

08:02.941 --> 08:04.860
Yes.

08:04.943 --> 08:07.946
I do not think that he and Meeka
will ever happen.

08:10.199 --> 08:12.409
Ever.

08:17.331 --> 08:20.667
IZZI:
There is Bopoto, my daughter.

08:20.751 --> 08:22.544
Perhaps your son can be...

08:22.628 --> 08:24.296
Uh, ay... (scoffs)

08:24.379 --> 08:26.465
But you don't have one.

08:26.548 --> 08:28.634
The shame must be unbearable,

08:28.717 --> 08:31.094
as a man, as a king,

08:31.178 --> 08:33.972
without an heir with a nut sack.

08:34.056 --> 08:36.558
(clicking tongue, groans)

08:36.642 --> 08:39.144
Thank you for your visit,
General.

08:39.228 --> 08:40.938
Seeing you brings to mind

08:41.021 --> 08:43.190
all of my father's
favorite curses for you.

08:44.775 --> 08:48.153
To call you a shit stain
brought him much joy.

08:48.237 --> 08:51.031
I advise you
to reconsider my offer.

08:51.114 --> 08:54.618
It is better to be bound
by blood and marriage

08:54.701 --> 08:58.997
than be divided
by blood and war.

09:00.791 --> 09:02.459
Eh?

09:02.542 --> 09:04.628
-(shouts in foreign language)
-(soldiers repeat shout)

09:04.711 --> 09:06.505
Hey!

09:06.588 --> 09:08.423
(footsteps marching)

09:14.263 --> 09:17.266
KING JAFFE JOFFER:
My time has come, my son.

09:17.349 --> 09:21.895
You must heed my words
before I'm gone.

09:21.979 --> 09:23.730
Please don't leave us so soon,
Your Highness.

09:23.814 --> 09:25.148
Zamunda needs you.

09:25.232 --> 09:27.025
Oh, shut up, Semmi!

09:27.109 --> 09:29.278
You don't have to suck up
to me anymore.

09:29.361 --> 09:30.821
I'll be dead soon.

09:30.904 --> 09:33.407
Why couldn't it be you, Semmi?

09:33.490 --> 09:34.783
BABA:
Yes, Your Majesty.

09:34.866 --> 09:36.868
His life is far too worthless.

09:36.952 --> 09:39.913
His death would make me smile.

09:39.997 --> 09:41.206
AKEEM:
Baba.

09:42.249 --> 09:43.292
(spits)

09:43.375 --> 09:45.794
The throne must pass
to a male heir.

09:45.877 --> 09:47.212
AKEEM:
Yes, Father.

09:47.296 --> 09:48.672
A male heir.

09:49.673 --> 09:51.383
Once again, I apologize to you

09:51.466 --> 09:54.011
for all of the shame
and disappointment

09:54.094 --> 09:56.555
that my offspring's
genetic makeup has caused you.

09:56.638 --> 10:01.768
My son, it appears
your shortcomings in masculinity

10:01.852 --> 10:04.104
have turned out to be unfounded.

10:04.187 --> 10:06.273
BABA:
I seen it

10:06.356 --> 10:08.150
in a vision.

10:09.526 --> 10:11.528
You gots a son.

10:13.947 --> 10:15.115
It is true.

10:16.283 --> 10:18.702
You have a son, Akeem.

10:20.704 --> 10:22.205
A bastard son.

10:22.289 --> 10:24.291
That is impossible.

10:24.374 --> 10:27.252
The only woman
I have ever lain with is Lisa.

10:27.336 --> 10:30.922
Father, I did not sow
my royal oats.

10:32.966 --> 10:34.343
JAFFE JOFFER:
Semmi!

10:34.426 --> 10:35.761
Hmm?

10:35.844 --> 10:38.263
Tell Akeem the truth at once.

10:42.267 --> 10:46.146
Remember in Queens,
night after night,

10:46.229 --> 10:48.315
you were looking
for the perfect woman?

10:48.398 --> 10:49.775
Yes.

10:49.858 --> 10:53.153
Well, I too was--
how can I say this?

10:54.738 --> 10:57.908
I was looking
for the perfect vagina.

11:00.452 --> 11:01.953
Or any vagina.

11:03.622 --> 11:07.084
We scoured the far reaches
of that loathsome city,

11:07.167 --> 11:09.753
searching rather unsuccessfully
for the woman of your dreams.

11:09.836 --> 11:12.464
(rapping): ♪ My name is Peaches,
and I'm the best ♪

11:12.547 --> 11:15.008
♪ All the DJs want
to feel my breast. ♪

11:15.092 --> 11:17.511
(deep voice): I've been
watching you all evening,

11:17.594 --> 11:19.971
and I want to tear you apart.

11:21.181 --> 11:22.974
And your friend, too.

11:25.727 --> 11:27.354
I am going to mingle.

11:27.437 --> 11:29.689
SEMMI:
I had had enough.

11:29.773 --> 11:32.776
And I realized, if I was ever
going to sow my oats

11:32.859 --> 11:34.319
on American soil,

11:34.403 --> 11:36.238
I was going to need
to find someone

11:36.321 --> 11:37.823
to take care of you.

11:37.906 --> 11:40.367
But don't worry,
I never broke our oath

11:40.450 --> 11:42.452
of keeping our identity
a secret.

11:42.536 --> 11:44.121
A prince?

11:45.163 --> 11:47.165
Yes, a prince.

11:47.249 --> 11:50.710
But he cannot know
that you know who he is.

11:50.794 --> 11:54.214
-We are undercover Africans.
-(women laughing)

11:54.297 --> 11:57.050
Africans undercover.
Oh, that's good, baby.

11:57.134 --> 11:59.886
You ain't got to lie like that
to get some of this ass.

11:59.970 --> 12:01.847
But you know what? I'll bump
uglies with your homeboy.

12:01.930 --> 12:04.516
Just let me go throw up
real quick, and, uh...

12:04.599 --> 12:07.561
and then we can, you know,
get it crackin'.

12:07.644 --> 12:11.231
♪ Let your soul glow... ♪

12:11.314 --> 12:13.859
SEMMI: I may not have been
thinking straight.

12:13.942 --> 12:16.027
In my defense, it had been weeks

12:16.111 --> 12:19.364
since the last time I was
tended to by the royal bathers.

12:19.448 --> 12:22.325
But at the time,
it seemed like a good plan.

12:22.409 --> 12:23.910
(woman laughing in other room)

12:25.454 --> 12:27.205
Mmm.

12:27.289 --> 12:30.917
I hope you like, uh,
pumpkin pie.

12:31.001 --> 12:34.629
'Cause you gonna get
a whole slice.

12:35.672 --> 12:36.882
(record scratches, music stops)

12:36.965 --> 12:39.426
That is not what happened,
Father.

12:39.509 --> 12:42.179
I remember meeting
this morally bereft woman,

12:42.262 --> 12:44.431
but there was
no inappropriate mating.

12:44.514 --> 12:46.600
She offered me
some of her ceremonial herbs.

12:48.393 --> 12:50.604
(coughing)

12:50.687 --> 12:51.938
(singsongy, echoing):
Princey.

12:52.022 --> 12:53.773
AKEEM:
And then, if memory serves,

12:53.857 --> 12:55.692
a wild boar burst into the room.

12:55.775 --> 12:58.028
It came and jumped into my lap.

12:58.111 --> 12:59.738
And then it began to ram me.

12:59.821 --> 13:02.491
-And ram me and ram me, ramming
and ramming! -(moans, laughs)

13:02.574 --> 13:04.367
And a foul...

13:09.247 --> 13:11.958
(screams)

13:12.042 --> 13:13.793
You fool,
what have you done to me?!

13:13.877 --> 13:15.462
-Go on, son.
-(Semmi choking)

13:15.545 --> 13:16.588
-Just kill him.
-Kill him!

13:19.299 --> 13:21.343
-So I actually have a son?
-A bastard son.

13:22.344 --> 13:23.845
-(kicks)
-(hawks, spits)

13:23.929 --> 13:26.848
Why was his existence
hidden from me all these years?

13:26.932 --> 13:31.353
I was hoping you would put
a stem on an apple of your own.

13:31.436 --> 13:36.149
The royal artist made a sketch
of my vision.

13:37.776 --> 13:40.487
This is your bastard.

13:40.570 --> 13:42.531
Hear me, Prince Akeem.

13:42.614 --> 13:46.284
General Izzi, he will use
the passing of our great king

13:46.368 --> 13:49.329
as a sign
to attack the weak one.

13:49.412 --> 13:51.873
The weak one?

13:51.957 --> 13:53.708
Am I the weak one?

13:53.792 --> 13:56.461
I spoiled you, my son.

13:56.545 --> 14:01.049
You are not strong
or ruthless as I am.

14:01.132 --> 14:03.426
You will be assassinated.

14:06.137 --> 14:07.389
Within a week.

14:07.472 --> 14:09.140
Month, tops.

14:09.224 --> 14:12.394
Prince Akeem,
follow the thunderbird.

14:12.477 --> 14:14.437
It will take you to your boy.

14:14.521 --> 14:15.897
Follow the thunderbird?

14:15.981 --> 14:17.440
This is madness.

14:17.524 --> 14:19.317
If my family were to ever
find out about this...

14:19.401 --> 14:21.111
You will be safe.

14:21.194 --> 14:24.072
Our people will be safe.

14:24.155 --> 14:27.492
It is the only way. You must.

14:30.620 --> 14:32.622
(labored breathing)

14:34.416 --> 14:35.667
Easy, my father.

14:35.750 --> 14:38.086
The end is near.

14:39.713 --> 14:41.923
My funeral...

14:42.007 --> 14:44.718
should be spectacular.

14:44.801 --> 14:45.802
(chuckles)

14:46.845 --> 14:48.638
Yeah, it will, Papa.

14:48.722 --> 14:53.226
Let's have it now
while I'm alive.

14:55.020 --> 14:57.063
It shall be glorious.

14:57.147 --> 14:59.065
♪ ♪

14:59.149 --> 15:01.192
MORGAN FREEMAN:
In the beginning,

15:01.276 --> 15:02.319
the universe began.

15:02.402 --> 15:06.031
Stars, planets,

15:06.114 --> 15:08.074
all the visible objects
in the universe

15:08.158 --> 15:12.746
came to be
with a single purpose:

15:12.829 --> 15:16.791
to prepare the way for
the grandest creation of all,

15:16.875 --> 15:19.753
the birth of Jaffe Joffer.

15:19.836 --> 15:21.838
(crowd cheering)

15:25.592 --> 15:26.801
FREEMAN:
But today,

15:26.885 --> 15:30.096
we gather for a moment or two

15:30.180 --> 15:32.390
to give much respect due

15:32.474 --> 15:36.353
to the king who made
a difference in our world.

15:36.436 --> 15:40.649
Zamundans, I give you...

15:40.732 --> 15:42.108
En Vogue.

15:42.192 --> 15:43.860
-Oh.
-(crowd gasps, cheers)

15:43.943 --> 15:45.445
-♪ Yeah, ooh ♪
-♪ What a king ♪

15:45.528 --> 15:46.821
♪ What a king, what a king ♪

15:46.905 --> 15:48.531
♪ What a mighty good king ♪

15:48.615 --> 15:50.408
♪ I'm-a say it again now ♪

15:50.492 --> 15:52.285
♪ What a king, what a king,
what a king ♪

15:52.369 --> 15:54.162
♪ What a mighty good king ♪

15:54.245 --> 15:55.747
♪ He's a mighty,
mighty good king... ♪

15:55.830 --> 15:58.291
And now... Salt-N-Pepa!

15:58.375 --> 16:00.043
(cheering)

16:00.126 --> 16:03.338
♪ My king is smooth like Barack,
but his voice got bass ♪

16:03.421 --> 16:05.507
♪ A Michael B. body
with a Denzel face ♪

16:05.590 --> 16:08.468
♪ Boss moves like Hov,
face on his own money ♪

16:08.551 --> 16:10.762
♪ He's good in every hood,
and he's got his own country ♪

16:10.845 --> 16:13.890
♪ He lookin' like a meal
every time I see him ♪

16:13.973 --> 16:17.018
♪ A lover and a leader,
other kings couldn't be him ♪

16:17.102 --> 16:19.604
♪ He dresses like a dapper don,
but even in jeans ♪

16:19.688 --> 16:22.065
♪ He's a godsent original,
the king of my dreams ♪

16:22.148 --> 16:23.650
-♪ Yeah, ooh ♪
-♪ What a king ♪

16:23.733 --> 16:25.610
♪ What a king, what a king,
what a king ♪

16:25.694 --> 16:27.278
♪ What a mighty good king ♪

16:27.362 --> 16:29.155
♪ So good, so good, so good ♪

16:29.239 --> 16:31.533
♪ What a king, what a king,
what a king ♪

16:31.616 --> 16:33.034
♪ What a mighty good king. ♪

16:33.118 --> 16:34.786
-(song ends)
-(cheering)

16:34.869 --> 16:37.580
(rhythmic drumbeat playing)

16:48.717 --> 16:50.218
(drumbeat ends)

16:50.301 --> 16:52.804
-MAN: Zamunda!
-(cheering)

16:56.224 --> 16:58.435
(somber music playing)

16:58.518 --> 17:01.479
With the passing
of the great king,

17:01.563 --> 17:04.566
the world changed forever.

17:05.900 --> 17:10.071
When he died,
no one ever smiled again.

17:10.155 --> 17:12.991
Vacations were canceled.

17:13.074 --> 17:14.576
Holidays ignored.

17:14.659 --> 17:16.202
GLADYS KNIGHT:
♪ He's leaving... ♪

17:16.286 --> 17:18.455
People didn't even
have sex anymore.

17:18.538 --> 17:19.956
(crowd gasping)

17:20.039 --> 17:22.125
(sniffling)

17:22.208 --> 17:26.629
Our great king
had gone away forever.

17:28.506 --> 17:29.966
Gladys Knight.

17:30.049 --> 17:32.719
♪ He's leaving ♪

17:32.802 --> 17:34.345
♪ Leaving ♪

17:34.429 --> 17:36.598
♪ On that midnight train ♪

17:36.681 --> 17:38.349
♪ From Zamunda ♪

17:38.433 --> 17:40.435
♪ Leaving on
the midnight train ♪

17:40.518 --> 17:42.187
-♪ Yes, he is ♪
-Son.

17:42.270 --> 17:44.063
Yes, my father.

17:44.147 --> 17:45.356
♪ Said he's going up ♪

17:45.440 --> 17:47.525
♪ Up, up, up, up ♪

17:47.609 --> 17:50.445
-♪ Going up to that great ♪
-Remember what I told you.

17:50.528 --> 17:52.530
♪ Sahara in the sky... ♪

17:52.614 --> 17:54.365
I'm going to die now.

17:54.449 --> 17:55.700
♪ Oh, yes, he is... ♪

17:55.784 --> 17:57.827
Come now, Father.
Everything is going to be...

17:57.911 --> 18:00.705
♪ Oh, please don't leave us ♪

18:00.789 --> 18:02.415
♪ Take us instead ♪

18:02.499 --> 18:05.502
♪ Take us on
that midnight train ♪

18:05.585 --> 18:07.086
-Father?
-♪ From Zamunda ♪

18:07.170 --> 18:09.672
