The boy must pass
the princely test.

45:56.838 --> 46:00.800
To forget the princely test
would be to spit in the faces

46:00.884 --> 46:04.137
of the great Joffers
who have come before you.

46:05.138 --> 46:06.764
Whose auntie is this?

46:08.224 --> 46:09.767
I give you a week.

46:09.851 --> 46:11.519
(drums play brief,
dramatic beat)

46:11.603 --> 46:14.564
I wouldn't want to go back
to plotting your death.

46:16.149 --> 46:17.233
Zoot!

46:17.317 --> 46:18.485
-SOLDIERS: Zoot!
-What's "zoot"?

46:18.568 --> 46:20.069
Y'all leaving?
Does that mean "leave"?

46:20.153 --> 46:22.322
(exclaims)

46:26.910 --> 46:29.370
I'll see you in one week,
my prince.

46:29.454 --> 46:31.080
LAVELLE:
A'ight.

46:32.874 --> 46:36.336
-Father, can we talk about this?
-There is nothing to talk about.

46:36.419 --> 46:38.838
MEEKA:
Nexdoria is our greatest threat.

46:38.922 --> 46:41.758
To broker a peace hinging on
the testosterone-clouded whims

46:41.841 --> 46:44.469
of a son you barely even know
is foolish.

46:44.552 --> 46:46.513
I said there is
nothing to talk about.

46:53.561 --> 46:55.021
(dramatic news theme plays)

46:55.104 --> 46:57.148
JAFFE JOFFER (over TV):
This is ZNN.

46:57.232 --> 46:58.775
Good evening, my neighbors.

46:58.858 --> 47:00.735
I'm Totatsi Bibinyana.

47:00.818 --> 47:03.029
In a most promising twist,

47:03.112 --> 47:05.865
the Zamunda News Network
has confirmed

47:05.949 --> 47:08.785
that King Akeem has a son.

47:08.868 --> 47:10.411
While it is too early
to determine

47:10.495 --> 47:12.664
whether the boy possesses
any strength, intelligence

47:12.747 --> 47:14.415
or capability whatsoever,

47:14.499 --> 47:17.210
what we do know
is that he is a man.

47:17.293 --> 47:19.963
And as far as Zamundan royalty
is concerned,

47:20.046 --> 47:21.548
that's good enough.

47:21.631 --> 47:23.299
♪ ♪

47:23.383 --> 47:24.592
The princely test
has three parts.

47:24.676 --> 47:26.135
-Okay. Uh-huh.
-Culture,

47:26.219 --> 47:29.722
critical thinking and,
more importantly, courage.

47:29.806 --> 47:31.266
AKEEM:
Where do we begin?

47:31.349 --> 47:35.603
Teach the young prince
how to walk like royalty.

47:35.687 --> 47:37.313
That is what we will do.

47:37.397 --> 47:40.024
We will teach you
how to walk like a prince.

47:40.108 --> 47:41.859
Yo, what's wrong
with the way I walk now?

47:41.943 --> 47:43.695
You walk like an American pimp.

47:43.778 --> 47:45.863
You dress like
a slave from the future.

47:45.947 --> 47:47.532
Old Jar Jar Binks lookin' ass.

47:47.615 --> 47:49.742
Here, in this hall,

47:49.826 --> 47:54.163
you will come face-to-face
with your Zamundan heritage.

47:54.247 --> 47:56.207
Let us begin.

47:57.208 --> 47:58.418
Jompu Joffer.

47:58.501 --> 47:59.794
Jampu...

47:59.877 --> 48:02.297
-Jakoof Joffer.
-Jujkoof...

48:02.380 --> 48:04.340
Mighty Jokeim Joffer,

48:04.424 --> 48:06.509
the most handsome
of all the Joffers.

48:08.303 --> 48:09.721
Clench your backside.

48:09.804 --> 48:12.181
-Put your shoulders back.
-Mm-hmm.

48:12.265 --> 48:13.391
-Put your chin up.
-Mm-hmm.

48:13.474 --> 48:16.060
Suck in your stomach
and walk thusly.

48:17.103 --> 48:18.896
Now? Walk? Okay.

48:20.023 --> 48:22.609
-This is a regal gait.
-Okay.

48:24.193 --> 48:25.653
Stop! Don't...

48:25.737 --> 48:27.447
Tuck in your backside.

48:27.530 --> 48:29.115
And who is this?

48:29.198 --> 48:30.366
Uh, that's Jappa Joffer.

48:30.450 --> 48:32.243
-No.
-Jabba the Hutt Joffer.

48:32.327 --> 48:34.579
-No.
-Jumpin' Jack Flash Joffer.

48:34.662 --> 48:35.705
(laughs):
No.

48:35.788 --> 48:37.290
-Gerald Levert Joffer?
-(laughing): No.

48:37.373 --> 48:39.125
-Jimmie "JJ" Walker Joffer?
-No.

48:39.208 --> 48:41.085
-Jabberwocky Joffer.
-No.

48:41.169 --> 48:42.170
LAVELLE:
James Brown Joffer.

48:42.253 --> 48:43.379
(imitates James Brown):
Hey!

48:43.463 --> 48:45.465
♪ ♪

48:50.762 --> 48:53.056
LAVELLE: All right, y'all,
what am I doing out here?

48:53.139 --> 48:54.474
I'm hungry. I'm...

48:54.557 --> 48:57.226
I-I'm late for my bath.
What am I looking for?

48:57.310 --> 48:58.978
-Hmm?
-(roars)

48:59.062 --> 49:01.272
Oh! That's a damn lion, bruh!

49:01.356 --> 49:04.692
Only when you can retrieve
the whiskers from a resting lion

49:04.776 --> 49:06.527
will you be ready
to become prince.

49:07.654 --> 49:11.157
(laughing)

49:11.240 --> 49:12.450
This is a joke.

49:12.533 --> 49:14.243
(stammering):
This is a joke, 'cause I know

49:14.327 --> 49:16.120
your soft ass ain't never
do nothing like that.

49:16.204 --> 49:17.872
Oh, yes, I did.

49:17.955 --> 49:20.833
-On my very first attempt.
-Well...

49:20.917 --> 49:23.836
Yes. First attempt. Very brave.

49:23.920 --> 49:26.047
AKEEM: You will need the courage
of all your ancestors...

49:26.130 --> 49:28.174
A machete? A rocket launcher?
What you got?

49:28.257 --> 49:30.635
...and the cunningness
of your Western ways.

49:30.718 --> 49:33.096
And these.

49:35.765 --> 49:37.767
(lion growling)

49:39.936 --> 49:41.729
Thank you.

49:47.860 --> 49:49.862
(growling softly)

49:51.406 --> 49:53.282
Ain't this a bitch.

49:54.492 --> 49:55.702
(thunder crashes)

49:55.785 --> 49:57.203
LAVELLE:
I just don't belong here.

49:57.286 --> 49:59.831
You are the son
of the king of Zamunda.

50:01.708 --> 50:03.584
You come from a long line
of Joffers, and...

50:03.668 --> 50:06.671
I come from a long line
of broke-ass nobodies.

50:08.131 --> 50:11.300
What the hell I was thinking
that I could have this?

50:11.384 --> 50:13.386
Or any of it?

50:14.595 --> 50:17.014
Hey, for real, just...
cut this off, all right?

50:17.098 --> 50:18.725
Just cut it off.

50:18.808 --> 50:20.351
(Mirembe sighs)

50:20.435 --> 50:23.146
You want to get rid of
the royal princely braid?

50:24.397 --> 50:26.858
Well, this is fair.

50:26.941 --> 50:30.361
To be honest, it wasn't
a great look on you.

50:31.696 --> 50:34.782
Just one of the many
backward Zamundan traditions.

50:36.284 --> 50:38.077
Hell yeah.

50:38.161 --> 50:40.705
How long have you felt that way?
You know how itchy this is?

50:40.788 --> 50:42.749
-It's a rat tail.
-(laughs)

50:42.832 --> 50:45.293
(laughs) And what's up
with y'all and lion whiskers?

50:45.376 --> 50:47.128
Like, be for real--
what's up with that?

50:47.211 --> 50:48.838
(Mirembe laughing)

50:48.921 --> 50:51.674
Hey, yo, I-I can't do this
right now, man.

50:54.469 --> 50:56.471
Yo, look where I'm at.

50:58.181 --> 51:00.224
I'm not supposed to be here.

51:01.267 --> 51:03.102
You know, my whole life,
I had dreams

51:03.186 --> 51:05.021
that my pops
would show up and take

51:05.104 --> 51:07.231
me and my mom away
to a whole new life.

51:07.315 --> 51:09.233
And come to find out,
he's a king.

51:09.317 --> 51:11.027
To a whole damn country.

51:11.110 --> 51:13.154
And the only way
to meet his expectations

51:13.237 --> 51:16.866
is to walk with a stick
up my ass or get myself killed.

51:18.993 --> 51:20.953
This-this ain't my way, Mirembe.

51:21.037 --> 51:24.624
And I-I-I can't... I can't be
what he wants me to be.

51:26.334 --> 51:30.087
Then perhaps
be not as King Akeem

51:30.171 --> 51:32.423
but as Prince Akeem.

51:34.091 --> 51:35.927
Ain't that the same brother?

51:37.094 --> 51:38.846
You haven't heard the story.

51:38.930 --> 51:41.390
Everyone in Zamunda knows

51:41.474 --> 51:45.228
the legend of Prince Akeem

51:45.311 --> 51:48.815
-in the land of Queens.
-(thunder crashes)

51:48.898 --> 51:51.442
Prince Akeem was
a dutiful prince

51:51.526 --> 51:53.152
and loyal son of Zamunda.

51:53.236 --> 51:54.278
AKEEM:
Hello, Babar.

51:54.362 --> 51:55.863
MIREMBE:
But he believed that a man

51:55.947 --> 51:57.907
must walk his own path
and follow his heart.

51:57.990 --> 51:59.742
I intend to find my bride.

51:59.826 --> 52:01.577
What is wrong
with the one you have now?

52:01.661 --> 52:03.496
-Bark like a dog.
-(barking)

52:03.579 --> 52:05.164
AKEEM:
I want a woman that's going to

52:05.248 --> 52:07.041
arouse my intellect
as well as my loins.

52:07.124 --> 52:09.085
MIREMBE:
He flew across the sea

52:09.168 --> 52:10.586
to find his true love.

52:10.670 --> 52:11.838
Now there,

52:11.921 --> 52:14.924
in the barbaric land of Queens

52:15.007 --> 52:18.344
did Prince Akeem battle
bug-eyed burglars,

52:18.427 --> 52:20.221
foul-mouthed barbers

52:20.304 --> 52:23.099
and sexist men of the cloth

52:23.182 --> 52:25.476
to win the heart
of his true love,

52:25.560 --> 52:28.271
Lisa McDowell of Queens.

52:28.354 --> 52:31.649
♪ To be loved, to be loved ♪

52:31.732 --> 52:34.610
♪ Oh, what a feeling ♪

52:34.694 --> 52:36.445
♪ To be loved... ♪

52:36.529 --> 52:38.614
MIREMBE:
The wedding was grand

52:38.698 --> 52:42.577
and beautiful and magical.

52:42.660 --> 52:45.454
A new dawn had arised
in Zamunda,

52:45.538 --> 52:46.873
a new sense of hope

52:46.956 --> 52:48.583
and change.

52:48.666 --> 52:51.419
King Akeem...

52:51.502 --> 52:54.130
may have forgotten his story,

52:54.213 --> 52:56.966
but the people of Zamunda
have not.

52:59.760 --> 53:02.513
(thunder crashes)

53:05.933 --> 53:07.977
Walk your own path.

53:08.060 --> 53:11.188
Be not the prince of Zamunda.

53:11.272 --> 53:13.733
Be the prince from Queens.

53:21.157 --> 53:24.619
("Smash the Crowd" by Public
Enemy, Ice-T and PMD playing)

53:24.702 --> 53:27.830
Lavelle Junson of Queens.

53:27.914 --> 53:29.707
-♪ Come on ♪
-♪ Haters gonna hate ♪

53:29.790 --> 53:32.126
♪ Fakers gonna fake,
breakers gonna break ♪

53:32.209 --> 53:34.086
♪ Neophytes gonna
make mistakes ♪

53:34.170 --> 53:37.506
♪ Sleepers gotta wake,
I'm-a say it again ♪

53:37.590 --> 53:40.343
♪ I'm-a say it loud,
give me a group, not one man ♪

53:40.426 --> 53:42.762
-♪ To smash the crowd, we... ♪
-(music stops)

53:42.845 --> 53:45.556
LAVELLE:
If it pleases Your Majesty,

53:45.640 --> 53:48.643
I present to you Kareem Junson,

53:48.726 --> 53:52.313
aka Uncle Reem,

53:52.396 --> 53:54.357
my royal consigliere.

53:54.440 --> 53:56.525
That's Italian
for "mack daddy mentor."

53:56.609 --> 53:59.779
You need no other teacher
than your king and your father.

53:59.862 --> 54:02.198
No, no, no, no. See, you watch
your bottom lip, money grip,

54:02.281 --> 54:03.824
'cause you understand,
while y'all was out here

54:03.908 --> 54:05.618
riding elephants
and chasing Tarzan,

54:05.701 --> 54:08.913
I was schooling this boy
on the streets of Queens.

54:08.996 --> 54:10.873
-All right, well, that's...
-No, 'cause he don't know me.

54:10.957 --> 54:13.250
-You do not know me.
-No, you don't know me.

54:13.334 --> 54:14.377
You do not know me.

54:14.460 --> 54:15.753
-You don't know me.
-I will cut you.

54:15.836 --> 54:17.004
Enough of this.

54:19.173 --> 54:23.469
Uncle Reem of Queens...
you're welcome in my kingdom.

54:23.552 --> 54:24.804
LAVELLE:
Come on.

54:24.887 --> 54:26.931
REEM: Benson, y'all got
some crab cakes, man?

54:27.014 --> 54:28.057
I need some protein.

54:28.140 --> 54:30.351
-Who is Benson?
-Benson is you.

54:30.434 --> 54:32.228
LAVELLE:
Hold up. Hold up.

54:32.311 --> 54:34.689
Let me get my Spotify
on deck real quick.

54:34.772 --> 54:36.399
("I'm a King" by Bobby Sessions
and Megan Thee Stallion playing)

54:36.482 --> 54:37.775
Let's rock.

54:37.858 --> 54:39.735
You ain't said nothing
but a thing.

54:39.819 --> 54:40.820
See his feet?

54:40.903 --> 54:42.113
-Yes.
-See where his hand at?

54:42.196 --> 54:43.864
-Mm-hmm.
-See how he moving?

54:43.948 --> 54:46.617
Yes. There's a fluidity to it.

54:46.701 --> 54:49.620
Yeah, it's like Bruce Lee said,
"Be like water."

54:49.704 --> 54:51.330
LAVELLE:
That's Hebbe Joffer.

54:51.414 --> 54:52.915
Legend has it
he could speak to animals,

54:52.999 --> 54:54.208
and people thought he was crazy

54:54.291 --> 54:56.002
until he made a giraffe
do the Electric Slide.

54:57.253 --> 54:59.213
TOTATSI (over TV):
It appears a royal wedding

54:59.296 --> 55:00.965
may soon be upon us.

55:01.048 --> 55:02.842
For more on this,
we are joined by Semmi.

55:02.925 --> 55:04.260
Good to see you, Totatsi.

55:04.343 --> 55:07.763
According to our ZNN source
inside the palace,

55:07.847 --> 55:09.765
we are hearing-- and I quote--

55:09.849 --> 55:13.769
"The boy been balling
on this princely-ass test

55:13.853 --> 55:18.607
ever since his handsome
and mad smart uncle showed up."

55:18.691 --> 55:21.152
That is absurd, Totatsi.
Who is your source?

55:21.235 --> 55:23.112
What the deal? What the deal?

55:23.195 --> 55:25.239
Palace life for me.

55:25.322 --> 55:26.949
SEMMI:
Who do you think you are, Reem,

55:27.033 --> 55:28.492
going behind the king's back?

55:28.576 --> 55:30.202
-You keep talking slick...
-G-Gentlemen.

55:30.286 --> 55:32.038
...and when my man
is running this place,

55:32.121 --> 55:33.873
you gonna go from
royal ass kisser

55:33.956 --> 55:35.708
-to royal ass wiper.
-No, no.

55:35.791 --> 55:37.501
-I will do no such thing.
-Please, g-gent...

55:37.585 --> 55:39.503
REEM: Yeah, well,
I eat a lot of fried food,

55:39.587 --> 55:40.880
so don't come at me with

55:40.963 --> 55:42.715
-anything less than two-ply.
-Oh!

55:42.798 --> 55:45.509
♪ I'm a queen, I'm a queen,
I'm a queen, I'm a queen ♪

55:45.593 --> 55:47.344
♪ Ain't nothing move
if they ain't got me ♪

55:47.428 --> 55:49.638
♪ I'm a queen, I'm a queen,
I'm a queen... ♪

55:49.722 --> 55:51.682
(laughing)

55:52.641 --> 55:54.351
Okay.

55:54.435 --> 55:56.812
♪ Run my bathwater, run the
kingdom, run it smarter... ♪

55:56.896 --> 55:58.856
Oh, that's right. Ooh!

55:58.939 --> 56:00.858
-I believe I have it now.
-Don't hurt nobody.

56:00.941 --> 56:02.276
LAVELLE:
Yeah, you got something.

56:02.359 --> 56:03.986
-Now let me hear you say,
"Hey, ho." -I don't know...

56:04.070 --> 56:05.529
-Hey, ho. -Oh.
-MARY: That's right.

56:05.613 --> 56:07.531
That's how we do it
in Queens, though.

56:07.615 --> 56:09.658
-Hey, ho.
-LAVELLE: Oh, no, no, no, no.

56:09.742 --> 56:11.035
No, don't do that.
That's his mother.

56:11.118 --> 56:12.620
-Oh, don't say it to...
-No, not to his mother.

56:12.703 --> 56:14.246
-You obese American, you.
-No. (stammers)

56:14.330 --> 56:15.706
Yeah, for 25 cents a day,

56:15.790 --> 56:18.417
I could sponsor-feed
your scrawny ass.

56:18.501 --> 56:20.336
Go to hell, you Western weasel!

56:20.419 --> 56:22.213
-Yo, well, why don't you go?
-Make me.

56:22.296 --> 56:23.964
You know something? Then I will.

56:24.048 --> 56:25.591
You cholesterol dumpster fire,
you.

56:25.674 --> 56:27.510
-(gasping, choking)
-I-- o-okay, okay.

56:27.593 --> 56:28.928
-Totatsi! Call the guards!
-(chuckles)

56:29.011 --> 56:30.221
Let us, let us go
for a short break.

56:30.304 --> 56:31.680
LAVELLE:
Hmm.

56:31.764 --> 56:32.932
That's Forest Whitaker.

56:33.015 --> 56:34.391
I'm joking. That's not...

56:34.475 --> 56:36.560
That one is Tunde Joffer.

56:36.644 --> 56:38.229
Uh, he's the reason why
the Zamundans migrated

56:38.312 --> 56:39.438
from the north to the east.

56:39.522 --> 56:41.023
TINASHE:
He's doing pretty good.

56:41.107 --> 56:43.609
Yeah? (grunts excitedly)

56:43.692 --> 56:45.694
♪ I'm a queen, I'm a queen,
I'm a queen, I'm a queen ♪

56:45.778 --> 56:48.322
♪ Ain't nothing move
if they ain't got me, ay ♪

56:48.405 --> 56:50.616
♪ I'm a queen, I'm a queen,
I'm a queen. ♪

56:50.699 --> 56:52.660
AKEEM: There is but one test
that remains:

56:52.743 --> 56:54.495
retrieving the whiskers
from a lion.

56:54.578 --> 56:56.288
(Lavelle sighs)

56:56.372 --> 56:59.917
My one question is:
How will you conquer your fear?

57:00.000 --> 57:01.627
I'm not.

57:01.710 --> 57:03.254
It's a damn lion.

57:03.337 --> 57:05.256
Well, I found it is helpful
to think of them

57:05.339 --> 57:07.007
as just being big house cats.

57:07.091 --> 57:08.592
-Oh?
-(chuckles)

57:08.676 --> 57:10.052
Just big house cats?

57:10.136 --> 57:12.304
Really?
When'd you figure that out?

57:12.388 --> 57:14.723
Was that on your tenth
or 11th try?

57:14.807 --> 57:16.433
I know not what you speak of.

57:16.517 --> 57:18.144
I was successful my first time,

57:18.227 --> 57:20.479
-just like my father.
-Jaffe Joffer.

57:20.563 --> 57:22.982
-And his father before him.
-Jappa Joffer.

57:24.024 --> 57:26.068
-Very good. Very good!
-(chuckling)

57:26.152 --> 57:27.361
(both laughing)

57:27.444 --> 57:29.488
-(elephant trumpeting)
-AKEEM: Oh, watch.

57:29.572 --> 57:31.031
-Oh, shit!
-Oh, do not be alarmed.

57:31.115 --> 57:32.825
This Babar, he is my friend.

57:32.908 --> 57:34.827
I have known him
since he was a small elephant.

57:34.910 --> 57:35.953
Let him pass. Move.

57:36.036 --> 57:37.246
-Let him pass.
-All right. (muttering)

57:37.329 --> 57:39.081
Come through, Babar, my friend.

57:39.165 --> 57:41.458
Babar, the magnificent one.

57:41.542 --> 57:44.003
I have known him
since he was a little elephant,

57:44.086 --> 57:45.880
and now he is a father, as well.

57:45.963 --> 57:47.506
-Wow.
-The great one!

57:47.590 --> 57:50.593
(Babar trumpeting)

57:52.219 --> 57:54.847
I must admit,
your manner and your style

57:54.930 --> 57:57.766
is foreign to my kingdom,
but it is impressive.

57:57.850 --> 58:01.478
Yeah? Damn, I'm just
trying to be like you.

58:01.562 --> 58:03.480
You know what I mean?

58:03.564 --> 58:06.400
You know, Mirembe,
my royal barber,

58:06.483 --> 58:08.777
told me the story that your pops

58:08.861 --> 58:10.988
wanted you to marry
a Nexdorian girl,

58:11.071 --> 58:14.200
so you bounced to Queens to find
a wife on your own terms.

58:16.368 --> 58:18.621
I wanted to find
more than a wife.

58:18.704 --> 58:22.249
To find someone that
I connected with on every level.

58:22.333 --> 58:24.168
Someone who knew
where I was coming from

58:24.251 --> 58:27.379
even though we came from
entirely two different places.

58:31.967 --> 58:34.720
And one might say I was
looking for myself, as well.

58:37.806 --> 58:40.893
Get some rest, my son.

58:42.811 --> 58:44.396
Thanks, Pops.

58:45.397 --> 58:47.691
♪ ♪

58:52.154 --> 58:54.156
(growling)

59:06.377 --> 59:08.295
He looks hungry.

59:08.379 --> 59:10.881
You can see it in how
he walks low to the ground.

59:10.965 --> 59:13.259
Look, man, you haven't liked me
since I got here,

59:13.342 --> 59:15.219
and I get that,
but ain't my fault

59:15.302 --> 59:18.013
your dad knocked up my mom and
dragged my ass back to Africa.

59:18.097 --> 59:20.557
Well, no one is
asking you to stay.

59:20.641 --> 59:22.476
It's all good, little sis.
All good.

59:22.559 --> 59:24.353
I'll be gone in a minute,
'cause I'm about to be

59:24.436 --> 59:25.729
-eaten by a lion!
-I hope so!

59:25.813 --> 59:26.897
-Fine! Fine!
-Fine!

59:29.608 --> 59:31.360
(growling softly)

59:34.071 --> 59:36.615
You really think
I'm gonna fail, don't you?

59:43.539 --> 59:45.874
I have never said that...

59:45.958 --> 59:47.876
out loud.

59:47.960 --> 59:49.837
You ain't got to.

59:49.920 --> 59:51.255
It's that look.

59:55.467 --> 59:58.012
Been getting that look
my entire life.

59:58.095 --> 1:00:01.265
People writing me off
'cause of the way I talk

1:00:01.348 --> 1:00:03.726
or where I'm from.

1:00:03.809 --> 1:00:05.811
But you got no idea
what I'm talking about.

1:00:05.894 --> 1:00:08.105
'Cause you a princess.

1:00:08.188 --> 1:00:11.859
Princesses can be written off
just as much as anyone.

1:00:11.942 --> 1:00:15.070
I have been preparing
my whole life

1:00:15.154 --> 1:00:17.865
to be standing where you are
in this moment.

1:00:19.450 --> 1:00:20.993
But you are right.

1:00:21.076 --> 1:00:22.911
It is not fair
for me to blame you

1:00:22.995 --> 1:00:25.289
for my father's mistake.

1:00:25.372 --> 1:00:27.833
Not that you are a mistake.

1:00:27.916 --> 1:00:29.835
-Well, you kind of are
a mistake. -Okay.

1:00:29.918 --> 1:00:31.879
I get it, I get it. A'ight.

1:00:31.962 --> 1:00:33.505
Damn.

1:00:34.965 --> 1:00:36.800
(chuckles)

1:00:38.677 --> 1:00:40.137
(growling softly)

1:00:40.220 --> 1:00:43.474
Perhaps the test has
nothing to do with bravery.

1:00:45.559 --> 1:00:49.772
The tests are also a challenge
of the mind.

1:00:55.027 --> 1:00:57.029
("Go Big" by YG playing)

1:01:01.367 --> 1:01:03.077
♪ Go big, go big ♪

1:01:03.160 --> 1:01:05.704
♪ Go big, go big,
go big, go big ♪

1:01:05.788 --> 1:01:07.831
♪ Go big, go big ♪

1:01:07.915 --> 1:01:09.458
♪ How big? Real big ♪

1:01:09.541 --> 1:01:11.335
♪ Sumo, fat crib
in the background ♪

1:01:11.418 --> 1:01:13.128
♪ Ad-lib, I'm in
the front row... ♪

1:01:13.212 --> 1:01:16.173
So, in sales, it's called
a bait and switch.

1:01:16.256 --> 1:01:18.300
So, the customer thinks
that they're buying something

1:01:18.384 --> 1:01:20.177
at half off,
so they come flocking,

1:01:20.260 --> 1:01:22.096
waving their wallets,
just hungry to buy something,

1:01:22.179 --> 1:01:23.972
but by the time they get there,

1:01:24.056 --> 1:01:26.100
you sell 'em the upgrade
at double the price.

1:01:26.183 --> 1:01:28.852
Yes. It is the same
as a technique

1:01:28.936 --> 1:01:31.522
we use in battle
called the feigned withdrawal.

1:01:31.605 --> 1:01:34.108
An army retreats
with the sole intention

1:01:34.191 --> 1:01:36.902
of drawing the enemy out
and ambushing him.

1:01:36.985 --> 1:01:39.405
So, what, in this scenario,
I'm-I'm the retreating army?

1:01:39.488 --> 1:01:41.573
No, you are the bait to switch.

1:01:42.991 --> 1:01:44.576
-♪ Say he winning, he lied ♪
-♪ Lied ♪

1:01:44.660 --> 1:01:46.161
-♪ I don't blame him, he tried ♪
-♪ Tried ♪

1:01:46.245 --> 1:01:47.663
-♪ I'm so fl-fl-fly ♪
-♪ I'm fly ♪

1:01:47.746 --> 1:01:49.331
-♪ I don't walk, I glide ♪
-♪ Glide ♪

1:01:49.415 --> 1:01:50.916
-♪ Don't need ice, we slide ♪
-♪ We slide ♪

1:01:50.999 --> 1:01:52.459
♪ Don't need ice, we slide ♪

1:01:52.543 --> 1:01:54.086
-♪ We slide ♪
-♪ I put in the time ♪

1:01:54.169 --> 1:01:56.088
-♪ Time ♪
-♪ Not like apple pie, sweet ♪

1:01:56.171 --> 1:01:57.631
♪ Go big, go big ♪

1:01:57.714 --> 1:02:00.884
♪ Go big, go big,
go big, go big ♪

1:02:00.968 --> 1:02:02.344
♪ Go big, go big. ♪

1:02:07.599 --> 1:02:09.184
REEM:
This ain't right.

1:02:09.268 --> 1:02:11.812
My nephew could be eaten
by a man-eating lion!

1:02:11.895 --> 1:02:13.814
Besides, what kind of kingdom
is this?

1:02:13.897 --> 1:02:17.985
I don't see no Lunchables or
no lunch trays up here, nothing!

1:02:19.611 --> 1:02:21.405
(lion purring softly)

1:02:31.039 --> 1:02:33.459
(panting quietly)

1:02:33.542 --> 1:02:35.127
(snaps)

1:02:35.210 --> 1:02:37.379
(growling)

1:02:40.340 --> 1:02:42.885
(moans, passes gas)

1:02:42.968 --> 1:02:45.262
(laughs quietly)

1:02:47.598 --> 1:02:49.308
(whistling)

1:02:50.851 --> 1:02:52.478
(imitating birdcall)

1:02:52.561 --> 1:02:53.979
(loudly imitates birdcall)

1:02:54.062 --> 1:02:55.522
(snarls)

1:02:55.606 --> 1:02:58.025
-(roars)
-No.

1:03:01.069 --> 1:03:02.154
Oh!

1:03:03.822 --> 1:03:04.990
(screams)

1:03:05.073 --> 1:03:06.825
Run! Run!

1:03:06.909 --> 1:03:08.869
Trust me, don't look back!

1:03:08.952 --> 1:03:10.454
Just keep running!
Keep running! Run!

1:03:10.537 --> 1:03:12.289
Keep running!

1:03:18.128 --> 1:03:20.464
-(screaming)
-(roaring)

1:03:23.217 --> 1:03:25.469
(gasping)

1:03:28.222 --> 1:03:29.723
No, no. No!

1:03:29.806 --> 1:03:31.183
(grunting)

1:03:31.266 --> 1:03:32.893
-(roaring)
-(screaming)

1:03:32.976 --> 1:03:35.145
He's trapped. I must save him.

1:03:35.229 --> 1:03:36.271
Stupid.

1:03:36.355 --> 1:03:37.356
Wait, Father.

1:03:38.524 --> 1:03:40.275
(lion growls)

1:03:40.359 --> 1:03:42.236
Look.

1:03:43.529 --> 1:03:45.531
(growling quiets)

1:03:46.657 --> 1:03:49.076
(chuckling softly)

1:03:49.159 --> 1:03:51.370
What is this?

1:03:51.453 --> 1:03:52.788
(groans)

1:03:52.871 --> 1:03:55.123
What is this?

1:03:55.207 --> 1:03:57.918
What every dangerous
house cat likes.

1:04:00.212 --> 1:04:01.421
Cat food.

1:04:10.264 --> 1:04:12.266
(panting)

1:04:14.476 --> 1:04:16.103
(laughs)

1:04:19.523 --> 1:04:22.109
(growls)

1:04:30.117 --> 1:04:32.119
♪ ♪

1:04:37.207 --> 1:04:39.501
-I got 'em. Mm-hmm.
-(cheering)

1:04:44.089 --> 1:04:46.133
He is almost ready
to become a prince.

1:04:46.216 --> 1:04:47.593
Wait, almost?

1:04:47.676 --> 1:04:49.219
(Lavelle stammers)

1:04:49.303 --> 1:04:53.140
It is time for umbajuntoo.

1:04:53.223 --> 1:04:55.892
-Umbajuntoo!
-CROWD: Umbajuntoo!

1:04:55.976 --> 1:04:58.520
(upbeat drumbeat playing)

1:05:04.985 --> 1:05:06.612
(drumbeat stops)

1:05:06.695 --> 1:05:09.406
Uh, what's-what's, uh...
umbajuntoo?

1:05:09.489 --> 1:05:11.950
Ceremonial circumcision.

1:05:12.034 --> 1:05:14.244
-Ceremonial...
-(drumbeat plays)

1:05:14.328 --> 1:05:15.829
That mean they're gonna
sharpen your tool, nephew.

1:05:15.912 --> 1:05:18.582
-Hold him. -Hey, yo,
ain't got to restrain me. Yo...

1:05:18.665 --> 1:05:20.500
-Hey, Ma, tell 'em we already
did this! -That's okay, baby.

1:05:20.584 --> 1:05:22.169
We love it here, right?

1:05:22.252 --> 1:05:24.129
Let them take a little bit
off the top.

1:05:24.212 --> 1:05:28.884
These are the foreskins
of your forefathers.

1:05:28.967 --> 1:05:31.219
-Ew.
-Joffer Joffer.

1:05:31.303 --> 1:05:33.138
Great-great-great-grandfather.

1:05:33.221 --> 1:05:35.182
Jappa Joffer.

1:05:35.265 --> 1:05:36.683
AKEEM:
Your great-grandfather.

1:05:36.767 --> 1:05:38.685
Jaffe Joffer.

1:05:38.769 --> 1:05:39.770
Your grandfather.

1:05:39.853 --> 1:05:43.357
And King Akeem.

1:05:43.440 --> 1:05:45.108
(drumbeat plays)

1:05:45.192 --> 1:05:46.610
(blade rings)

1:05:48.945 --> 1:05:50.781
Okay.

1:05:50.864 --> 1:05:52.866
-(rapid drumbeat playing)
-(crowd clapping rhythmically)

1:05:59.039 --> 1:06:01.583
(Baba yells)

1:06:01.667 --> 1:06:03.627
(screams)

1:06:03.710 --> 1:06:05.837
(sobbing loudly)

1:06:07.089 --> 1:06:09.424
(Baba giggling)

1:06:09.508 --> 1:06:12.594
What are you...
Oh, what is wrong with you?

1:06:12.678 --> 1:06:14.513
-(groaning, whimpering)
-(Baba giggling)

1:06:14.596 --> 1:06:16.098
See, a potato.

1:06:16.181 --> 1:06:19.101
(laughter)

1:06:22.979 --> 1:06:26.233
They got you, baby!
They got you! (laughing)

1:06:27.609 --> 1:06:30.612
You just completed
the final princely test,

1:06:30.696 --> 1:06:33.240
-the test of courage.
-Courage?

1:06:33.323 --> 1:06:35.492
Need I remind you
I was face-to-face

1:06:35.575 --> 1:06:36.827
with a man-eating lion?

1:06:36.910 --> 1:06:39.162
For one to put
his member in danger

1:06:39.246 --> 1:06:41.915
is also a test of courage, yes?

1:06:41.998 --> 1:06:45.085
You are willing to sacrifice
what is most sacred.

1:06:45.168 --> 1:06:46.753
My penis?

1:06:46.837 --> 1:06:48.714
Your pride.

1:06:48.797 --> 1:06:49.923
(sighs)

1:06:50.006 --> 1:06:52.217
Lavelle Junson of Queens,

1:06:52.300 --> 1:06:55.679
I hereby crown you

1:06:55.762 --> 1:06:58.223
the prince of Zamunda.

1:06:59.224 --> 1:07:01.643
(crowd gasping, murmuring)

1:07:03.270 --> 1:07:05.814
Okay, so you thought
the best response was

1:07:05.897 --> 1:07:07.607
to let them cut it off?

1:07:07.691 --> 1:07:09.609
I was doing whatever it took.

1:07:09.693 --> 1:07:11.445
Like what, exactly?

1:07:11.528 --> 1:07:13.947
Well, to prove myself.

1:07:14.030 --> 1:07:15.949
You know, like,
I-I never really got

1:07:16.032 --> 1:07:17.576
the chance to do that back home.

1:07:20.454 --> 1:07:22.038
(Mirembe clears throat)

1:07:23.248 --> 1:07:25.333
As you were.

1:07:25.417 --> 1:07:27.127
(laughing)

1:07:27.210 --> 1:07:30.297
I take it you are growing
accustomed to a palace life.

1:07:30.380 --> 1:07:32.132
I mean...

1:07:32.215 --> 1:07:35.802
aside from some insane rituals
y'all have here,

1:07:35.886 --> 1:07:38.889
I suppose life here
ain't too bad.

1:07:41.558 --> 1:07:43.477
(chuckles)

1:07:43.560 --> 1:07:45.812
-MIREMBE: Well, there are
certain disadvantages. -Uh-huh.

1:07:45.896 --> 1:07:47.731
-I mean, have you seen
a Zamundan movie? -Mm-mm.

1:07:47.814 --> 1:07:49.649
-Total baboon dung.
-(laughs)

1:07:49.733 --> 1:07:52.778
So, what, like, nothing
over a 30% on Rotten Papayas?

1:07:52.861 --> 1:07:54.279
-Ah.
-(chuckles)

1:07:54.362 --> 1:07:56.490
American cinema is the best.

1:07:56.573 --> 1:07:58.492
The best? That is, like,

1:07:58.575 --> 1:08:00.869
the most blasphemous thing
I've ever heard. (chuckles)

1:08:00.952 --> 1:08:03.079
What do we have
besides superhero shit,

1:08:03.163 --> 1:08:07.334
uh, remakes and-and sequels
to old movies nobody asked for?

1:08:07.417 --> 1:08:09.211
This is true about sequels.

1:08:09.294 --> 1:08:10.712
If something is good...

1:08:10.796 --> 1:08:12.130
BOTH:
...why ruin it?

1:08:12.214 --> 1:08:13.465
LAVELLE:
Mm.

1:08:13.548 --> 1:08:15.884
-Although there are exceptions.
-Like what?

1:08:15.967 --> 1:08:17.928
Are you familiar
with the Barbershop series?

1:08:18.011 --> 1:08:19.805
Am I familiar with...
(stammers) Look at me.

1:08:19.888 --> 1:08:22.265
Of course I'm familiar
with the Barbershop series.

1:08:22.349 --> 1:08:26.311
My favorite spin-off is
the one with Queen Latifah.

1:08:26.394 --> 1:08:28.855
Yeah, but that's not Barbershop.

1:08:28.939 --> 1:08:31.441
That's Beauty Shop.

1:08:31.525 --> 1:08:34.277
To-mah-to, to-may-to.

1:08:34.361 --> 1:08:36.363
Potato, papaya.

1:08:37.531 --> 1:08:38.740
(sucks teeth)

1:08:40.283 --> 1:08:42.452
So, what,
American entertainment?

1:08:42.536 --> 1:08:44.538
Is that our biggest difference?

1:08:45.956 --> 1:08:47.749
Well...

1:08:47.833 --> 1:08:51.503
there are certain freedoms
that exist outside of Zamunda.

1:08:51.586 --> 1:08:53.255
Okay.

1:08:53.338 --> 1:08:54.965
Like what?

1:08:56.842 --> 1:08:59.427
Okay, this is
going to sound stupid,

1:08:59.511 --> 1:09:02.556
but it has always been
a dream of mine to...

1:09:02.639 --> 1:09:04.641
to one day have
my own barbershop.

1:09:05.684 --> 1:09:06.768
Yo, that's awesome.

1:09:08.103 --> 1:09:09.729
Are you making fun of me?

1:09:09.813 --> 1:09:11.356
No.

1:09:11.439 --> 1:09:13.191
Nah, I'm being dead-ass.

1:09:13.275 --> 1:09:14.776
Do it.

1:09:14.860 --> 1:09:16.987
I-I don't know anybody
who can work scissors like you.

1:09:17.070 --> 1:09:19.281
Well, except
women are not allowed

1:09:19.364 --> 1:09:20.991
to own businesses in Zamunda.

1:09:21.074 --> 1:09:23.034
You serious?

1:09:23.118 --> 1:09:24.536
Indeed.

1:09:24.619 --> 1:09:26.580
That's not cool.

1:09:28.206 --> 1:09:30.667
Well, I'm prince, right?

1:09:30.750 --> 1:09:32.335
So, you know something?

1:09:32.419 --> 1:09:34.504
As long as I'm prince,

1:09:34.588 --> 1:09:37.299
I can promise you there's gonna
be some changes around here.

1:09:37.382 --> 1:09:40.093
Well, that is very idealistic.

1:09:40.176 --> 1:09:42.888
But every prince... (sighs)

1:09:42.971 --> 1:09:45.140
promises to do things
differently,

1:09:45.223 --> 1:09:47.726
but eventually, they do things

1:09:47.809 --> 1:09:49.811
the same way they've always
been done before.

1:09:51.062 --> 1:09:54.065
Yeah, well, I'm not like
every other prince.

1:09:54.149 --> 1:09:56.192
Remember?

1:09:56.276 --> 1:09:58.153
I'm a prince from Queens.

1:09:59.195 --> 1:10:02.032
I wonder who told you that.

1:10:02.115 --> 1:10:04.492
Somebody.

1:10:13.752 --> 1:10:16.338
I should not have done that.

1:10:16.421 --> 1:10:18.548
-I should not have done that.
-Wait. Wait, hold on.

1:10:18.632 --> 1:10:20.050
Mirem...

1:10:20.133 --> 1:10:21.760
Um...

1:10:23.261 --> 1:10:26.306
I think it is best you go to bed
and get some rest.

1:10:27.390 --> 1:10:29.726
Tomorrow is going to be
a very long day.

1:10:29.809 --> 1:10:32.604
You are one step closer to...

1:10:32.687 --> 1:10:34.898
marrying your princess.

1:10:38.693 --> 1:10:40.320
Good night.

1:10:52.040 --> 1:10:54.459
♪ ♪

1:10:59.255 --> 1:11:02.926
Presenting the crown prince
of Zamunda,

1:11:03.009 --> 1:11:04.928
Prince Lavelle!

1:11:05.011 --> 1:11:06.930
(cheering and applause)

1:11:07.013 --> 1:11:09.015
♪ ♪

1:11:20.610 --> 1:11:21.695
(mouthing)

1:11:25.240 --> 1:11:26.533
("Koroba" by Tiwa Savage
playing)

1:11:26.616 --> 1:11:28.702
(chuckling)

1:11:28.785 --> 1:11:30.495
-King Akeem.
-Yes.

1:11:30.578 --> 1:11:32.163
So wonderful to see you,
General.

1:11:32.247 --> 1:11:33.832
(chuckling)

1:11:33.915 --> 1:11:35.041
(both chuckling)

1:11:35.125 --> 1:11:36.543
IZZI:
Ooh.

1:11:36.626 --> 1:11:38.211
(chuckles)

1:11:38.294 --> 1:11:40.296
-Prince Lavelle.
-General Izzi.

1:11:40.380 --> 1:11:43.216
Please, allow me to reintroduce

1:11:43.299 --> 1:11:47.137
my daughter, Bopoto!

1:11:47.220 --> 1:11:50.015
♪ Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey-hey ♪

1:11:50.098 --> 1:11:52.100
♪ ♪

1:11:53.476 --> 1:11:55.395
♪ Hey, hey ♪

1:11:55.478 --> 1:11:58.356
♪ Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey-hey ♪

1:11:58.440 --> 1:12:02.402
♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh-ooh ♪

1:12:02.485 --> 1:12:06.156
-♪ Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey... ♪
-♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh-ooh... ♪

1:12:06.239 --> 1:12:08.658
My prince.

1:12:08.742 --> 1:12:12.078
Perhaps you two should get to
know each other a little better.

1:12:12.162 --> 1:12:13.204
Yes.

1:12:13.288 --> 1:12:15.832
("These Streets"
by Mi Casa playing)

1:12:15.915 --> 1:12:21.629
♪ Good morning to the world
out there... ♪

1:12:21.713 --> 1:12:23.381
Oh.

1:12:24.424 --> 1:12:26.801
Lovely. (chuckles)

1:12:26.885 --> 1:12:29.179
Hey, dig this here.

1:12:29.262 --> 1:12:33.892
Could I get two Crown Royals
for me and my royal compadre?

1:12:33.975 --> 1:12:35.393
Compadre?

1:12:35.477 --> 1:12:37.187
It means "friend."

1:12:38.229 --> 1:12:40.356
I am Uncle Reem's friend.

1:12:40.440 --> 1:12:41.649
Yes, you are.

1:12:42.692 --> 1:12:43.902
Cheers.

1:12:43.985 --> 1:12:45.779
How you doing? Hey, ladies.

1:12:45.862 --> 1:12:47.405
How you doing? Mm.

1:12:47.489 --> 1:12:48.823
I know I look good.

1:12:48.907 --> 1:12:50.325
Mm, a makeover.

1:12:50.408 --> 1:12:52.077
My hair is on point.

1:12:52.160 --> 1:12:54.287
New dress. Who this?

1:12:54.370 --> 1:12:56.164
Well, if you're
going to wear that dress,

1:12:56.247 --> 1:12:57.999
then you should wear this.

1:12:58.083 --> 1:13:02.045
♪ That we have in this life ♪

1:13:02.128 --> 1:13:03.254
♪ These streets... ♪

1:13:03.338 --> 1:13:05.340
Oh, my God.

1:13:05.423 --> 1:13:07.008
Are you serious?

1:13:07.092 --> 1:13:08.676
Yes. Turn around.

1:13:08.760 --> 1:13:10.345
Oh, my goodness.

1:13:10.428 --> 1:13:12.138
(chuckling):
Oh.

1:13:13.431 --> 1:13:15.558
I can't believe it.
This is so beautiful.

1:13:15.642 --> 1:13:17.519
I know you gonna want this back.

1:13:17.602 --> 1:13:18.603
It's a gift.

1:13:18.686 --> 1:13:19.854
You're family now.

1:13:19.938 --> 1:13:21.523
(chuckles)

1:13:21.606 --> 1:13:23.274
-Let's go get drunk.
-What?

1:13:23.358 --> 1:13:26.361
MARY: Yes, girl, me and you
'bout to turn it up.

1:13:26.444 --> 1:13:28.029
Hey, bartender!

1:13:28.113 --> 1:13:30.240
Let me have some of
your finest drink.

1:13:30.323 --> 1:13:32.367
Two shots of chilled Cîroc.

1:13:32.450 --> 1:13:34.452
♪ ♪

1:13:37.872 --> 1:13:41.292
So, uh... marriage.

1:13:41.376 --> 1:13:42.919
It's a big step.

1:13:43.962 --> 1:13:46.548
I will make you a happy prince.

1:13:50.301 --> 1:13:51.845
What about you?

1:13:51.928 --> 1:13:54.556
How can I make you
a happy princess?

1:13:54.639 --> 1:13:56.432
What do you like?

1:13:56.516 --> 1:13:59.519
Whatever you like.

1:14:00.562 --> 1:14:02.230
Okay, I'll back up.

1:14:02.313 --> 1:14:06.151
Uh, Bopoto,
what's your favorite movie?

1:14:06.234 --> 1:14:09.737
Whatever is your favorite movie.

1:14:09.821 --> 1:14:12.240
Uh... is there a goal you have?

1:14:12.323 --> 1:14:14.701
Is-is there a business
that you want to start?

1:14:14.784 --> 1:14:17.704
Whatever business
you'd like to start.

1:14:27.088 --> 1:14:31.134
I want to have a connection
with the person

1:14:31.217 --> 1:14:34.387
that I'm gonna spend
the rest of my life with.

1:14:34.470 --> 1:14:36.973
But I am just a wife.

1:14:43.897 --> 1:14:45.982
-Can you wait right here?
-Okay.

1:14:46.065 --> 1:14:48.151
-But what shall I do?
-Just wait.

1:14:48.234 --> 1:14:49.944
Right here.

1:14:51.321 --> 1:14:53.072
I shall wait here.

1:14:54.073 --> 1:14:55.783
Okay.

1:14:55.867 --> 1:14:57.660
BOTH: ♪ Stop what you're doing
'cause I'm about to ruin ♪

1:14:57.744 --> 1:14:59.871
♪ The image and the style
that you're used to ♪

1:14:59.954 --> 1:15:02.582
♪ I look funny, but, yo,
I'm making money, see ♪

1:15:02.665 --> 1:15:04.584
♪ So, yo, world, I hope
you're ready for me ♪

1:15:04.667 --> 1:15:05.752
(laughing)

1:15:05.835 --> 1:15:07.503
♪ The Humpty Dance ♪

1:15:07.587 --> 1:15:09.923
♪ Is your chance
to do the Hump ♪

1:15:10.006 --> 1:15:12.217
♪ Uh, oh, do me, baby ♪

1:15:12.300 --> 1:15:15.136
♪ Do the Humpty Hump,
do the Humpty Hump ♪

1:15:15.220 --> 1:15:17.222
♪ Oh, do me, baby. ♪

1:15:17.305 --> 1:15:18.765
Everything is coming out...

1:15:18.848 --> 1:15:20.808
Hey, um, I don't mean
to interrupt,

1:15:20.892 --> 1:15:23.770
but, Mutombo, do you mind
if I have a minute with her?

1:15:23.853 --> 1:15:25.146
My bad, man.

1:15:25.230 --> 1:15:27.065
No, no, no.

1:15:27.148 --> 1:15:28.608
It's your party, Prince.

1:15:28.691 --> 1:15:30.610
Come here, you gentle giant.
(sighs)

1:15:30.693 --> 1:15:32.654
Yeah.

1:15:32.737 --> 1:15:34.864
I need to talk to you.

1:15:36.074 --> 1:15:37.951
There's nothing for us
to talk about.

1:15:38.034 --> 1:15:39.285
Excuse me.

1:15:39.369 --> 1:15:40.620
Yes, there is.

1:15:40.703 --> 1:15:42.830
I don't want to marry her.

1:15:43.915 --> 1:15:45.917
♪ ♪

1:15:50.213 --> 1:15:52.465
I want to be with you.

1:15:54.092 --> 1:15:57.303
You and only you are
the reason why I'm a prince.

1:15:57.387 --> 1:15:59.514
But, Lavelle...

1:15:59.597 --> 1:16:00.974
Look.

1:16:01.975 --> 1:16:03.851
My father...

1:16:03.935 --> 1:16:05.520
he'll understand.

1:16:07.522 --> 1:16:09.274
I'll be right back.

1:16:13.403 --> 1:16:16.739
I must say, you are more like
your father than I thought.

1:16:16.823 --> 1:16:19.033
Oh, really?
Why do you say that, General?

1:16:19.117 --> 1:16:21.369
Snatching up this bastard boy
from America

1:16:21.452 --> 1:16:24.330
and throwing him
into our kingly affairs...

1:16:24.414 --> 1:16:27.041
(laughs) like a chess pawn?

1:16:27.125 --> 1:16:29.335
(Izzi laughing)

1:16:29.419 --> 1:16:32.171
Your pawn just took
a future queen,

1:16:32.255 --> 1:16:34.716
and now there can be peace.

1:16:34.799 --> 1:16:36.843
And profit.

1:16:38.469 --> 1:16:40.096
Well played, King Akeem.

1:16:40.179 --> 1:16:42.098
Well played.

1:16:42.181 --> 1:16:44.392
(Izzi laughing)

1:16:49.105 --> 1:16:51.899
I need to find my mom.
I need to find my Uncle Reem.

1:16:53.067 --> 1:16:55.278
We got to bust out
of this bullshit, man.

1:16:55.361 --> 1:16:57.280
Wh-Why? Where are we going?

1:16:57.363 --> 1:16:58.823
Home.

1:17:00.325 --> 1:17:02.243
A home...

1:17:02.327 --> 1:17:05.705
A home that we can build
together.

1:17:16.382 --> 1:17:18.384
(playing upbeat tune)

1:17:24.349 --> 1:17:26.434
Uh, where is Prince Lavelle?

1:17:26.517 --> 1:17:29.604
My prince asked me to stay here
about an hour ago.

1:17:33.816 --> 1:17:37.820
Prince Lavelle Junson was seen
fleeing with the royal groomer.

1:17:37.904 --> 1:17:39.655
And he took his Uncle Reem

1:17:39.739 --> 1:17:41.282
and that wretched woman
with him, as well.

1:17:41.366 --> 1:17:43.034
Show respect.

1:17:43.117 --> 1:17:45.119
She is still
the mother of my son.

1:17:45.203 --> 1:17:47.497
She took the royal jet.

1:17:47.580 --> 1:17:49.248
That thieving bitch.

1:17:49.332 --> 1:17:50.833
IZZI:
King Akeem.

1:17:51.876 --> 1:17:53.836
Where is your prince?

1:17:53.920 --> 1:17:55.588
Ah, I do believe he has gone

1:17:55.671 --> 1:17:57.799
for one of his, um,
evening strolls.

1:17:57.882 --> 1:18:00.051
He does that from time to time
to clear his mind.

1:18:00.134 --> 1:18:01.636
Oh.

1:18:01.719 --> 1:18:04.180
I hope he's not getting
cold feet.

1:18:04.263 --> 1:18:06.516
-Nonsense.
-(Izzi chuckles)

1:18:06.599 --> 1:18:08.017
Good.

1:18:08.101 --> 1:18:11.145
Because I will be expecting
a wedding tomorrow.

1:18:11.229 --> 1:18:12.688
Of course.

1:18:14.190 --> 1:18:16.526
(chuckles)

1:18:16.609 --> 1:18:19.821
IZZI:
Wedding bells, wedding bells.

1:18:21.781 --> 1:18:23.825
Everything that I have
done for him,

1:18:23.908 --> 1:18:25.576
I can't believe
he has done this.

1:18:25.660 --> 1:18:27.995
I make him a prince,
I give him a chance to finally

1:18:28.079 --> 1:18:30.540
make something of himself,
and this is how he repays me!

1:18:30.623 --> 1:18:34.168
(slurring): I finally made
a friend from my own hood,

1:18:34.252 --> 1:18:36.045
and now she's gone.

1:18:36.129 --> 1:18:39.674
(whimpers)
Oh, I'm-a miss her crazy ass.

1:18:39.757 --> 1:18:41.551
He could've told me
about this groomer.

1:18:41.634 --> 1:18:44.345
But, no, instead he runs off
to America without a word to me.

1:18:44.429 --> 1:18:47.682
It is the most selfish act,
unworthy of a Joffer!

1:18:47.765 --> 1:18:49.392
It is spineless!

1:18:49.475 --> 1:18:51.769
Like father, like son.

1:18:51.853 --> 1:18:53.396
What did you say?

1:18:53.479 --> 1:18:55.440
-Uppity bitch say what?
-What?

1:18:55.523 --> 1:18:57.525
(laughing)

1:18:58.693 --> 1:19:01.237
You are intoxicated, my queen.

1:19:01.320 --> 1:19:03.489
All kinds of
wiggity-wack stuff happens

1:19:03.573 --> 1:19:06.367
when you are drunk and high,

1:19:06.451 --> 1:19:10.079
including making babies

1:19:10.163 --> 1:19:14.250
that you don't know
anything about.

1:19:14.333 --> 1:19:16.669
Right now you are getting
very in and out of my pocket.

1:19:16.752 --> 1:19:19.672
Are you trying to say
I'm out of pocket?

1:19:19.755 --> 1:19:21.883
What I am saying is, when a
person is drunk, they may say

1:19:21.966 --> 1:19:23.426
-something that they regret...
-So, whenever a woman

1:19:23.509 --> 1:19:24.927
speaks her mind, including
our daughter, then you just...

1:19:25.011 --> 1:19:26.220
...so I suggest
you mind your tongue!

1:19:29.974 --> 1:19:32.018
What happened to you, Akeem?

1:19:32.101 --> 1:19:36.063
You were supposed to
change things.

1:19:36.147 --> 1:19:39.525
You were supposed to bring this
kingdom to the 21st century,

1:19:39.609 --> 1:19:43.946
but instead,
you push our daughter aside,

1:19:44.030 --> 1:19:49.035
someone who has dedicated
her life to this country.

1:19:49.118 --> 1:19:51.621
And because she's a woman,

1:19:51.704 --> 1:19:53.915
she can't be your heir?

1:19:53.998 --> 1:19:57.001
I cannot ignore
hundreds of years of tradition.

1:19:57.084 --> 1:19:58.669
I am the ruler of this land.

1:19:58.753 --> 1:20:00.421
I must be strong.

1:20:05.343 --> 1:20:06.761
I get it.

1:20:08.262 --> 1:20:10.431
You're the king.

1:20:10.515 --> 1:20:12.642
Well, I'll tell you what.

1:20:12.725 --> 1:20:15.770
There are a lot of other beds
in this castle.

1:20:16.771 --> 1:20:19.982
I suggest you find another one.

1:20:20.066 --> 1:20:24.362
Would you dare banish me
from my own bedroom?

1:20:24.445 --> 1:20:26.155
Are you a fool?

1:20:26.239 --> 1:20:29.742
Do you see me hopping on one leg
and barking like a dog?

1:20:56.060 --> 1:20:57.728
What the hell is going on here?

1:20:57.812 --> 1:20:59.355
He's in the back.

1:20:59.438 --> 1:21:01.649
He's been here for hours.

1:21:07.405 --> 1:21:08.656
Akeem.

1:21:10.825 --> 1:21:12.868
How you doing, son?

1:21:14.120 --> 1:21:16.163
I used to quite enjoy mopping.

1:21:16.247 --> 1:21:18.666
It was simple,
and it made sense.

1:21:23.004 --> 1:21:25.923
Every day, I have moved
closer to the comfort of life,

1:21:26.007 --> 1:21:28.050
and now my eyes are open,

1:21:28.134 --> 1:21:29.969
and the man that
I always wanted to be

1:21:30.052 --> 1:21:31.679
is on the other side
of the world.

1:21:31.762 --> 1:21:33.306
Lavelle.

1:21:33.389 --> 1:21:36.892
Yes, he has fleed to America
for love just as I did.

1:21:36.976 --> 1:21:38.728
And now,
because of my stubbornness,

1:21:38.811 --> 1:21:40.771
I have run off my own son.

1:21:42.064 --> 1:21:43.774
Failed him as a father.

1:21:43.858 --> 1:21:46.402
You're not just a father.

1:21:46.485 --> 1:21:48.112
You're the king.

1:21:48.195 --> 1:21:51.198
And heavy lies the head
that wears the crown.

1:21:51.282 --> 1:21:53.993
Yes, I understand
that expression more now.

1:21:54.076 --> 1:21:56.537
It's not so much the crown
that is so heavy.

1:21:56.621 --> 1:22:00.041
It's everything
that comes with it. Hmm?

1:22:00.124 --> 1:22:01.834
You've got your country to run

1:22:01.917 --> 1:22:04.754
and a crazy-ass general
breathing down your neck.

1:22:04.837 --> 1:22:06.672
And on top of all that,

1:22:06.756 --> 1:22:09.508
you got to be
a husband and a father.

1:22:09.592 --> 1:22:11.719
Yes, you can see
that is most troubling.

1:22:11.802 --> 1:22:13.512
-Oh, I get it.
-Of course you get it.

1:22:13.596 --> 1:22:15.598
You are the king
of your own castle.

1:22:15.681 --> 1:22:18.100
And the troubles never stop,
Akeem.

1:22:18.184 --> 1:22:20.227
When I introduced the McFlurby,

1:22:20.311 --> 1:22:21.979
the McDonald's lawyers
came after me

1:22:22.063 --> 1:22:24.565
the same way this General Izzi
is coming after you.

1:22:24.649 --> 1:22:28.235
Cease-and-desist letters,
copyright infringement.

1:22:28.319 --> 1:22:32.448
I mean, the McFlurby
is nothing like the McFlurry.

1:22:32.531 --> 1:22:35.326
We put our toppings
on the bottom.

1:22:36.786 --> 1:22:38.371
So you have to stay strong.

1:22:38.454 --> 1:22:40.289
And you have to put
McDowell's first.

1:22:40.373 --> 1:22:42.917
-I am McDowell's.
-And I am Zamunda.

1:22:43.000 --> 1:22:44.293
It's not the Golden Arches.

1:22:44.377 --> 1:22:46.420
BOTH:
It's the Golden Arcs.

1:22:46.504 --> 1:22:47.838
And I'm the boss.

1:22:47.922 --> 1:22:50.007
And I am the MF'ing king.

1:22:50.091 --> 1:22:51.342
You damn right you are.

1:22:51.425 --> 1:22:54.261
Cleo, thank you.

1:22:54.345 --> 1:22:57.056
I much needed to hear
the wisdom of a father.

1:22:57.139 --> 1:22:58.891
Well, I'm sure your father
would understand

1:22:58.974 --> 1:23:01.310
-what you're going through.
-Yes.

1:23:04.021 --> 1:23:05.022
Akeem.

1:23:06.607 --> 1:23:09.318
What do you think
your mother would say now?

1:23:10.528 --> 1:23:12.405
My mother?

1:23:12.488 --> 1:23:14.365
The queen.

1:23:14.448 --> 1:23:18.619
I always thought that she was
the wisest of all the Joffers.

1:23:18.703 --> 1:23:21.122
What do you think
she would say to you now, son?

1:23:21.205 --> 1:23:23.207
♪ ♪

1:23:31.173 --> 1:23:32.675
Zamundans, rise.

1:23:32.758 --> 1:23:34.135
Prepare the royal jet.

1:23:34.218 --> 1:23:35.636
I shall return to America

1:23:35.720 --> 1:23:37.805
and retrieve
this errant child of mine.

1:23:37.888 --> 1:23:39.765
General Izzi will return
in one day,

1:23:39.849 --> 1:23:43.060
and if there's no wedding,
he most certainly will attack.

1:23:43.144 --> 1:23:45.104
You stay here
and protect my family.

1:23:45.187 --> 1:23:47.523
I'm no warrior, Your Majesty.

1:23:47.606 --> 1:23:48.941
Remember who you are.

1:23:49.024 --> 1:23:50.484
You are a son of Zamunda.

1:23:50.568 --> 1:23:52.570
Be strong.

1:23:54.572 --> 1:23:56.574
♪ ♪

1:23:58.492 --> 1:24:00.411
CLARENCE: And I'll tell you
something else.

1:24:00.494 --> 1:24:02.079
I only like redbone gals.

1:24:02.163 --> 1:24:04.582
Oh, see, that's where we part.
I like my women Black.

1:24:04.665 --> 1:24:05.875
I want a woman so Black,

1:24:05.958 --> 1:24:07.626
when you make love,
you need a flashlight.

1:24:07.710 --> 1:24:09.211
I'm looking for
the good stuff, man.

1:24:09.295 --> 1:24:10.546
CLARENCE:
Hey! Mufasa!

1:24:10.629 --> 1:24:12.965
Hey, I hear you got
your boy back.

1:24:13.048 --> 1:24:14.842
My son has returned to Queens.

1:24:14.925 --> 1:24:16.093
It is most urgent
that I find him.

1:24:16.177 --> 1:24:17.636
You know, he was here
a little while ago

1:24:17.720 --> 1:24:19.472
with a fine little, pretty
African thing. Wasn't she fine?

1:24:19.555 --> 1:24:21.891
-Mm-hmm! -Yeah, talking about
getting her a job here.

1:24:21.974 --> 1:24:23.684
Then they gonna
save up her money.

1:24:23.768 --> 1:24:25.686
-Then she gonna get
her own place. -That's right.

1:24:25.770 --> 1:24:27.313
I told her she could start
right now, she was so fine.

1:24:27.396 --> 1:24:29.482
-That's right. -But, she-- they
had to go off to their nuptials.

1:24:31.233 --> 1:24:32.651
Nuptials?

1:24:32.735 --> 1:24:34.278
-Yeah.
-Where?

1:24:34.361 --> 1:24:35.780
Near that Chinese restaurant

1:24:35.863 --> 1:24:37.573
where I caught the runs
last Saturday.

1:24:37.656 --> 1:24:39.158
-What?
-Oh, King Yum's.

1:24:39.241 --> 1:24:40.326
Gentlemen,
I have no time for this.

1:24:40.409 --> 1:24:42.328
That egg foo yong
made me have to stop off

1:24:42.411 --> 1:24:45.498
at my sister's last week
and make an emergency dump.

1:24:45.581 --> 1:24:47.082
Silence!

1:24:47.166 --> 1:24:48.584
I have no time to listen
to your stories

1:24:48.667 --> 1:24:49.794
about your bowel movements.

1:24:49.877 --> 1:24:51.837
Where is the ceremony?

1:24:51.921 --> 1:24:54.423
-Church of Holy Jubilation.
-Thank you.

1:24:55.716 --> 1:24:57.843
You're welcome.

1:25:00.137 --> 1:25:02.598
Who the hell he think
he talking to? Coming in here...

1:25:02.681 --> 1:25:04.350
Just 'cause he a king.
I got a dog named King.

1:25:04.433 --> 1:25:05.601
Yeah, he ain't
the king of this shop.

1:25:05.684 --> 1:25:07.394
-I'm the king of this shop.
-Exactly.

1:25:07.478 --> 1:25:09.730
He was nicer
when he was a prince.

1:25:09.814 --> 1:25:11.607
(indistinct chatter)

1:25:11.690 --> 1:25:13.692
(sirens whooping in distance)

1:25:16.904 --> 1:25:19.031
Is this a pious house of God?

1:25:19.114 --> 1:25:21.575
If "pious" means cheap,
well, then you right.

1:25:21.659 --> 1:25:23.619
This the best house of God
we could find

1:25:23.702 --> 1:25:24.995
on a Tuesday afternoon.

1:25:25.079 --> 1:25:26.872
So let's get these rings
on these fingers

1:25:26.956 --> 1:25:28.999
before the all-day shrimp
ends at Sizzler's.

1:25:29.083 --> 1:25:30.793
I don't even know why
they call it "all-day."

1:25:30.876 --> 1:25:32.044
It ends at 6:00.

1:25:32.127 --> 1:25:33.629
Look, baby,
it's about the love, okay?

1:25:33.712 --> 1:25:35.297
Not the shrimp.

1:25:35.381 --> 1:25:36.966
-What's a Sizzler?
-It's nothing.

1:25:39.969 --> 1:25:42.388
♪ ♪

1:25:48.227 --> 1:25:52.064
I assume the prince has returned
from his midnight stroll

1:25:52.147 --> 1:25:55.442
and is prepared
to marry my daughter.

1:25:55.526 --> 1:25:58.237
My apologies, General.

1:25:58.320 --> 1:26:01.782
Prince Lavelle is
currently indisposed.

1:26:01.866 --> 1:26:03.701
Indisposed?

1:26:03.784 --> 1:26:05.786
Really?

1:26:05.870 --> 1:26:08.539
I will not continue
to be jerked around

1:26:08.622 --> 1:26:10.541
like a howler monkey

1:26:10.624 --> 1:26:13.127
grazing in a field
of horny goat weeds.

1:26:13.210 --> 1:26:17.006
Now, you tell me,
where is King Akeem?

1:26:17.089 --> 1:26:18.966
♪ ♪

1:26:30.519 --> 1:26:32.146
REVEREND:
All right.

1:26:32.229 --> 1:26:34.064
Let's get hitched.

1:26:34.148 --> 1:26:35.774
-(lights buzzing)
-♪ Hallelu... ♪

1:26:35.858 --> 1:26:37.359
Let there be light.

1:26:37.443 --> 1:26:38.527
Hey!

1:26:39.987 --> 1:26:43.824
We are gathered here today

1:26:43.908 --> 1:26:48.120
for the meeting
of these two beautiful souls,

1:26:48.203 --> 1:26:52.166
pressed together
like a pair of sumptuous...

1:26:53.208 --> 1:26:54.627
...beings.

